id: jf-lpki
title: Enforce docstring and static analysis quality gates
description: "Require complete high-quality source API documentation and strict non-bypassable checks for TypeScript safety, docstrings, duplication, pm metadata, dependencies, containers/filesystems, shell scripts, PowerShell, CodeQL/Greptile, and coverage reporting."
type: Feature
status: in_progress
priority: 0
tags[4]: code-quality,docs,security,static-analysis
created_at: "2026-07-21T19:13:36.782Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T20:10:30.387Z"
assignee: codex-jellyfin
author: codex-jellyfin
estimated_minutes: 720
acceptance_criteria: "Every exported and internal source declaration has accurate actionable API documentation and docstring coverage is 100 percent; No any, inline/dynamic imports, non-erasable TypeScript syntax, or untyped external APIs remain; ESLint, jscpd, pm validation/lint, Trivy, ShellCheck, PSScriptAnalyzer where applicable, CodeQL, Greptile, and Codecov are mandatory documented gates; All tools are pinned, free to run in GitHub, and cannot be silently skipped when applicable files exist"
goal: jf-mqpo
value: Turn project quality policy into executable and reviewable guarantees.
impact: "Prevents undocumented, duplicated, insecure, or weakly typed changes from entering main."
outcome: A strict local and CI quality pipeline with 100 percent documentation evidence.
why_now: The new mandatory policy expands the release contract beyond runtime correctness and coverage.
parent: jf-gn5j
reviewer: maintainer
risk: critical
confidence: medium
sprint: jellyfin-10.11.11
blocked_by: jf-mkzh
dependencies[5]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  jf-mkzh,blocked_by,"2026-07-21T19:13:36.782Z",codex-jellyfin,null
  jf-59hr,related_to,"2026-07-21T19:50:11.875Z",codex-jellyfin,null
  jf-gqxo,related_to,"2026-07-21T19:50:11.875Z",codex-jellyfin,null
  jf-sylm,related_to,"2026-07-21T19:50:11.875Z",codex-jellyfin,null
  jf-wemh,related_to,"2026-07-21T19:50:11.875Z",codex-jellyfin,null
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:52:47.903Z",codex-jellyfin,"Current quality evidence: typecheck and strict ESLint pass; every source file is at or below 300 code lines excluding comments; tracked-tree and repository-history secret scans pass. jscpd reports a 5.78% duplicated-line baseline, so zero-duplication and the complete mandatory gate bundle remain open work."
  "2026-07-21T20:04:31.266Z",codex-jellyfin,"Strict TypeScript and JSDoc lint, source LOC, and both secret scans pass. The zero-duplication command is now explicit as check:duplicates, but remains red at the measured 5.78% baseline and is intentionally not represented as a completed release gate."
  "2026-07-21T20:09:41.945Z",codex-jellyfin,"Dependency remediation completed for the current lane: compatible overrides pin vite 8.1.5, flatted 3.4.2, postcss 8.5.21, esbuild 0.28.1, and picomatch 4.0.5; both bun audit and npm audit now report zero vulnerabilities. Typecheck, lint, and all 903 non-live tests still pass."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:13:36.782Z",codex-jellyfin,"Applicability must be explicit: ShellCheck/PSScriptAnalyzer gates fail on violations when matching scripts exist and report a deterministic no-files result otherwise."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:16:03.605Z",codex-jellyfin,"Current policy scan found two inline type imports and one parameter-property class; no explicit any types or dynamic imports were found in src. Existing ESLint treats no-explicit-any and unused declarations as warnings and disables the any rule in tests, so it is not yet a mandatory gate."
files[4]{path,scope,note}:
  bun.lock,project,Resolved vulnerability-free Bun dependency graph
  eslint.config.js,project,Mandatory type-safety erasable-syntax and JSDoc rules
  package-lock.json,project,Reproducible audited npm compatibility dependency graph
  package.json,project,Strict lint plugins duplication command and audited transitive overrides
tests[3]{command,path,scope,timeout_seconds}:
  bun audit,bun.lock,project,120
  bun run typecheck && bun run lint,eslint.config.js,project,300
  npm audit --omit=dev,package.json,project,120
body: ""
